The Setback: The Collapsed Tunnel
After defeating the apparitions, the party faces the real challenge of this section: the tunnel is blocked, and the direct route is impassable.
The Problem:
 The main tunnel they need is completely blocked by rubble and unstable support beams. They have three options:
Option 1: Clear the Rubble (Very Hard -4 Might Check, 1 Hour)
 The party can attempt to carefully clear the rubble and shore up the supports. This is extremely difficult and time-consuming.
Success: They clear a path, but the noise and time (1 hour = 1 FP drain) alerts everything in the barrow. All future encounters have enemies with Advantage on initiative.
Failure: The tunnel collapses further, dealing 2d6 damage to the character attempting it and making this route permanently impassable.
Option 2: Find the Hidden Passage (Standard Guile Check)
 A character searching carefully can find what the miners discovered before they diedΓÇöa natural fissure in the wall behind some equipment that leads to an older section of the barrow.
Success: They find the passage and can squeeze through carefully (requires a Standard Agility check to navigate safely).
Failure: They don't notice the passage initially but can try again or attempt another option.
Option 3: Blast Through with Magic (Hard -2 Magic Check)
 A mage can attempt to use destructive magic to clear the rubble forcefully.
Success: A controlled blast clears the rubble, though it's loud and alerts the barrow.
Failure: The uncontrolled blast causes a partial collapse, dealing 3d6 damage to everyone in the area and making the route impassable.
GM Note: Option 2 (finding the hidden passage) is the "intended" solution and should be the most rewarding. It's a test of perception and careful exploration, not brute force.
