Phase Transition (When Reduced to 20 HP or Less):
 When the Pale Lady is bloodied, she becomes desperate and changes tactics:
She immediately uses her Ice Storm ability (even if already used)
Her movement is no longer hindered by the ice (she glides across it supernaturally)
She focuses all attacks on whoever dealt the most damage to her
Tactics:
Phase 1 (40-21 HP): The Queen's Wrath
 The Pale Lady advances slowly from her throne, projecting regal menace. She uses her Two Attacks to focus on the most heavily armored character, attempting to overwhelm them with sustained damage. She positions herself to maximize her Frost Aura, trying to catch multiple party members in its radius.
The Draugr Guardians move to flank and intercept anyone trying to reach the Pale Lady directly, creating a defensive line.
Phase 2 (20-1 HP): Desperate Fury
 When bloodied, the Pale Lady's composure shatters. She unleashes her Ice Storm immediately, targeting as many party members as possible. After this, she fights recklessly, using Two Attacks each round against whoever has dealt the most damage to her, ignoring tactical positioning in favor of pure offense.
If reduced to 5 HP or less, she attempts to retreat to her throne and may try to bargain (see Optional Roleplay below).
Draugr Guardians
Stats (Each):
