GM Note: The Hidden Truth
For the GM Only (Do Not Share with Players):
Old Bjorn is the unawakened Dragonborn. He possesses a Dragon Soul that remains dormant because he never attended his execution at HelgenΓÇöthe event that would have triggered his awakening.
His "Luck" Is Actually Fate:
 The reason Bjorn always seems to be heading where the party needs to go, why he's never been killed by bandits despite traveling alone, why people instinctively trust him, why he's lived to old age in a dangerous worldΓÇöall of this is his dormant Dragon Soul subtly influencing reality around him. Fate itself arranges for him to be in the right place at the right time.
Players Won't Know:
 To the party, Bjorn is just a convenient NPC who provides fast travel and logistics support. They'll think he's a "game mechanic NPC" that lets them skip boring travel sequences. They have no reason to suspect he's anything more than a friendly, competent merchant.
The Long Game:
 Bjorn will travel with the party throughout Act I, becoming a recurring companion and friend. He'll witness their adventures, provide support, and become part of the group's dynamic. When Act II begins (after the party reaches Expert Tier), High King Torygg will formally hire Bjorn as the Wardens' dedicated cart driver, making his presence official.
Much, much later (Act IV), the party will discover the truth about who Bjorn really is, and that discovery will change everything.
But for now? He's just a friendly merchant who makes travel easier.

